cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with defining and comparing expressive power of different concurrency models, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another likely category as the paper defines standard notions from other concurrency models for ST(C)-structures, which can be seen as a programming language. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with defining and studying structures (ST-structures and STC-structures) and their properties. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with concurrency models, which is a relevant topic in software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with automata and their expressive power.
